    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Outside Ducasse's Doors</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Elizabeth Grossman letter comments on William Grimes's July 12 article on new Manhattan restaurant operated by Alain Ducasse</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a gesture toward mitigating the let-them-eat-cake extravagance of the price of a meal at the new Alain Ducasse restaurant described by  William Grimes in ''The Perfect Tempest: A Sneak Preview of Ducasse'' (July 12), perhaps diners there -- or the restaurant itself -- could somehow be persuaded to donate an equivalent sum to an organization devoted to ending hunger and poverty.</p>
        <p>ELIZABETH GROSSMAN  Portland, Ore.</p>
      </block>
